🔥 Correct Architecture Explanation (How a Pro Speaks)
1️⃣ Application Flow

When a request comes:

Client → Route → Middleware → Controller → Model → Database → Response

That is the lifecycle.

🧠 Register Flow (Refined Version)

Client sends:

POST /user/register

Steps:

Route receives request

Validation middleware checks input

Controller:

Check if email already exists

Hash password using bcrypt

Create user in database

Send 201 response

Important:
Password is never returned because schema has select: false.

That is professional explanation.

🧠 Login Flow (Refined)

Client sends:

POST /user/login

Steps:

Validate input

Find user by email (explicitly select password)

Compare hashed password using bcrypt

If valid → generate JWT

Send token + user info

JWT is stored on client side.

Server remains stateless.

🧠 Protected Route Flow

Client sends request with:

Authorization: Bearer <token>

Steps:

Middleware extracts token

Verify token using secret

Decode user ID

Fetch user from DB

Attach user to req.user

Allow controller to execute

If token invalid → 401.

